08/07/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Regional army chiefs met Monday (July 7th) in the Turkish resort of Antalya to discuss promoting military co-operation in the region.
Present were the chiefs of the general staffs of Romania, Montenegro, Serbia, Macedonia, Greece, Turkey, Bulgaria, Albania and Bosnia and Herzegovina, as well as NATO and EU military committee representatives.
The participants underlined the importance of good neighbourly relations and military co-operation among Balkan states to address regional security challenges.
Participants approved a number of joint military activities in coming years.
The next meeting of Balkan army chiefs will occur in Serbia in 2009.
(Zaman, Hurryiet - 08/07/08, Turkish Press, MIA, Anadolu news agency - 07/07/08)
